{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7050ea6c-9b84-4758-ab41-f3d665c0d916","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. The flow is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --hotreload\n```\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest infrastructure and does **not** support the hot reload extension. Since your project already has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled, `dotnet run` will launch the testing platform directly, watch for file changes, and re-run affected tests automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e4df14d3-e30e-4090-b6e3-e5ae8bae418b","outputTokens":139},"id":"2ce13f62-cb9a-4603-834b-e3850326be77","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:47.477Z","parentId":"6902ad39-fba8-4d7f-bbd8-ff24a4f563ee"}
